  "title": "Electrician | Troubleshooting",
  "description": "<p>Our client is in <strong>Marine and Offshore Industry.</strong> </p><p>Location: West (Company transport provided)<br />Working Hour: Monday - Friday, 8.30am - 6pm<br />Salary: $2,000 to $2,500 + VB</p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Inspect electrical panels and systems to detect and resolve issues or malfunctions.</li><li>Perform regular testing to ensure proper operation and compliance with safety standards.</li><li>Verify that electrical panels and systems meet required standards and specifications.</li><li>Maintain documentation of panel specifications, wiring diagrams, and system configurations.</li><li>Coordinate with the shipyard for installation, commissioning, and testing of electrical systems and panels.</li><li>Conduct hands-on testing, troubleshooting, and commissioning of supplied electrical systems and panels.</li><li>Collaborate with internal and external stakeholders to ensure systems pass all relevant class surveys and inspections.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Able to read drawings and terminate central cables.</li><li>Strong troubleshooting and problem-solving skills for Electrical switchboard.</li></ul><p><em>Interested candidates who wish to apply for the advertised position, please click </em><em><strong>APPLY NOW</strong></em><em> or email an updated copy of your resume/cv.</em><br /><em>We regret that only shortlisted candidate will be notified.</em></p><p><em>Email Address: </em><a href=\"mailto:jobs@recruitpedia.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><em>jobs@recruitpedia.sg</em></a></p><p><em>Recruitpedia Pte. Ltd.</em><br /><em>EA License No: 19C9682</em><br /><em>EA Personnel No: R25157233 (Loh Pooi Keng)</em></p>",
